The pearl-clutchers better get used to it.”ADADTrump insisted Wednesday that he did nothing improper in the Stone case.
“I didn’t speak to them, by the way, just so you understand,” the president told reporters, referring to Justice Department officials.
Still, a chorus of former U.S. attorneys and former Justice Department leaders condemned Trump for what they consider improper political pressure in a criminal prosecution.
There is a precedent of at least one Senate Republican trying to contain Trump’s handling of the Justice Department.
On Stone’s case, conservative media commentators may have played a role in spurring Trump to action.